#X text 1450 116 pause&play makes sure that all the speakers stop playing when the fear threshold is met. They take in a bang (after 15 seconds of increased playspeed has happened. This abstraction then pauses every speaker \, continues it after the frustration sound and then slowly increases the volume., f 61;
#X obj 1450 59 cnv 15 232 45 empty empty pause&play 20 20 0 40 #b7b7b7 #373737 0;
#X obj 1450 228 cnv 15 249 45 empty empty death\ trigger 20 20 0 40 #b7b7b7 #373737 0;
#X text 1450 288 the death trigger abstration stops the speakers from playing \, play's the panic sound and makes sure that the speaker doesn't get turned on again., f 61;
#X obj 314 1886 cnv 15 322 45 empty empty speed\ regulator 20 20 0 40 #b7b7b7 #373737 0;
#X text 314 1946 the speed regulator takes in all the different readings from the arduinio communication patch. It passes it on to the fear pause calculation patch. after the required pause is calculated it puts out a number of messages. These messages regulate how fast the speakers should play \, when they need to continue \, when they need to pause and how long they have to wait, f 61;
#X text 3261 2315 this adds distortion when someone gets close to the speaker, f 33;
#X text 2934 611 this part makes sure that the continue message of the pause&play abstraction has to wait for the appropriate time if that speaker was currently pausing (so it could get in sync) before it can continue, f 37;
#X obj -317 1658 cnv 15 857 44 empty empty look\ in\ this\ abstraction\ for\ further\ explanation\ --> 20 20 0 40 #b7b7b7 #373737 0;
#X msg 2442 2185 pgm \$1 3;
#X msg 2925 2190 pgm \$1 4;
#X text 1147 1954 this bang makes the bass notes 1 octave higher so that they're actually audible, f 22;
#X text 1594 2037 all these object here allow you to change the pitch and volume of the speaker, f 16;
#X text 1618 2316 The fear threshold abstractions send the proper values to the bitcrusher object to that the speakers sound more distorted as they get scared, f 38;
